# Admin Card Reordering Feature

Add up/down arrow buttons and position numbers to every card in all 6 Admin Dashboard sections, giving the admin full control over display order.

## Design Approach

Following the reference image's pattern (numbered items + up ▲ / down ▼ arrow buttons), each card in every section will get:

1. **Position Number** — A bold numbered badge (e.g., `#1`, `#2`, `#3`) on the left side of every card, so the admin immediately sees the display order.
2. **Up/Down Arrow Buttons** — Two small `ChevronUp` / `ChevronDown` buttons next to each card. Clicking swaps the item with its neighbor above or below. The first item's "Up" button and the last item's "Down" button are disabled (grayed out).
3. **Instant Persistence** — Every swap immediately updates the portfolio context array, which auto-syncs to Firestore. No separate "Save Order" step needed.

## Proposed Changes

### Component: AdminDashboard

#### [MODIFY] [AdminDashboard.tsx](file:///e:/Portfolio/Nityam-Patel-Portfolio/src/components/AdminDashboard.tsx)

**1. Add `ChevronUp`, `ChevronDown` to Lucide imports** (line 3-7)

**2. Add a reusable `moveItem` helper function** (near line 100)
```tsx
function moveItem<T>(arr: T[], fromIndex: number, direction: 'up' | 'down'): T[] {
  const toIndex = direction === 'up' ? fromIndex - 1 : fromIndex + 1;
  if (toIndex < 0 || toIndex >= arr.length) return arr;
  const newArr = [...arr];
  [newArr[fromIndex], newArr[toIndex]] = [newArr[toIndex], newArr[fromIndex]];
  return newArr;
}
```

**3. Add reorder functions for each section:**
- `reorderProjects(index, direction)` → calls `portfolio.setProjects(moveItem(...))`
- `reorderSkills(index, direction)` → calls `portfolio.setTechnologies(moveItem(...))`
- `reorderCerts(index, direction)` → calls `portfolio.setCertificates(moveItem(...))`
- `reorderHacks(index, direction)` → calls `portfolio.setHackathons(moveItem(...))`
- `reorderExps(index, direction)` → calls `portfolio.setExperiences(moveItem(...))`
- `reorderEdus(index, direction)` → calls `portfolio.setEducations(moveItem(...))`

**4. Update all 6 section card renderings:**

For each `.map()` call, change from `.map(item =>` to `.map((item, index) =>` and add:
- A numbered position badge `#1`, `#2`, etc. on the left
- Up/Down arrow buttons between the position badge and the card content
- Disable up arrow on first item, down arrow on last item

Example card row structure (applies to all 6 sections):
```
[#1] [▲] [▼] [Card Content...] [Edit] [Delete]
```

## Sections Affected

| Section | Array | Line (`.map()`) | Grid Layout |
|---|---|---|---|
| Projects | `portfolio.projects` | ~1274 | `grid-cols-1` |
| Skills | `portfolio.technologies` | ~1560 | `grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2` |
| Certifications | `portfolio.certificates` | ~1725 | `grid-cols-1` |
| Hackathons | `portfolio.hackathons` | ~1896 | `grid-cols-1` |
| Experiences | `portfolio.experiences` | ~2130 | `grid-cols-1` |
| Education | `portfolio.educations` | ~2284 | `grid-cols-1` |

> [!NOTE]
> **Skills section** currently uses a 2-column grid (`sm:grid-cols-2`). For the reordering to make visual sense (item 1 is top-left, item 2 is top-right, etc.), I'll change it to a **single-column layout** in the Admin Dashboard only. The public-facing portfolio Skills grid remains unchanged.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `npm run build` — verify zero compilation errors.

### Manual Verification
- Open Admin Dashboard, verify position numbers appear on all cards in all 6 sections.
- Test up/down arrow buttons — verify cards swap positions correctly.
- Verify first item's up and last item's down buttons are disabled.
- Verify the reordered list persists after closing and reopening the Admin Dashboard.
